          "date": "2018-01-09 04:42:38.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-10438 mdt: layout truncate compatibility",
        "message": "LU-10438 mdt: layout truncate compatibility\n\nFLR change the protocol to instantiate layout before truncate\nrequest. This patch makes old server understand 2.11+ clients'\ntruncate write intent request.\n\nIn PFL design, client issues [0, size) intent to MDS to instantiate\nobjects in this extent. While in FLR design, the intent servers two\npurposes: 1) make objects across [size, EOF) on other mirrors stale,\nand 2) instantiate objects in the chosen write mirror. And FLR\nchooses to use [size, EOF) as the extent of truncate write intent\nrequest.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam.xu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I12d90320ba704f01457670f864d78fe764233000\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_10"
    }
